channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: June 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The US-backed Gaza ceasefire proposal doesn't meet Hamas' demands for an end to the war, a senior official has told CNN. Osama Hamdan also said that "no one has an idea" how many of the hostages held in the enclave are alive.

item.title: Micro communities for the homeless sprout in US cities eager for small, quick and cheap solutions
item.description: In downtown Atlanta, shipping containers have been transformed into an oasis for dozens of previously unsheltered people who now proudly call a former parking lot home

item.title: Violent road-rage fight at L.A. airport leaves elderly woman unconscious
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: 6/13: CBS Evening News
item.description: State of emergency declared in South Florida as relentless rainfall causes major flooding; Milwaukee school farms seek to address food insecurity

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy.

item.title: An NYPD inspector tried to cover up his date's drunken crash, prosecutors say
item.description: A New York Police Department inspector has been indicted on charges that he lied to investigators and tried to get incriminating video footage erased after his girlfriend drunkenly crashed his police car into a cab

item.title: Justice Thomas’ former clerk reacts to claim that he took more trips on GOP megadonor’s private plane
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Judge halts new Title IX LGBTQ student protections in 4 states
item.description: The judge called the Title IX rule expanding LGBTQ protections for students a "threat to democracy," temporarily blocking it Louisiana, Mississippi, Montana and Idaho.

item.title: Supreme Court maintains access to abortion pill in unanimous decision
item.description: The Supreme Court has issued a decision on whether the US Food and Drug Administration overstepped its authority by expanding access to the abortion pill mifepristone.

item.title: WATCH: Bear destroys car’s interior after breaking into vehicle — and then takes a nap
item.description: A Canadian woman found a bear taking a nap inside the vehicle and said her husband opened the door to let the trapped animal escape. The next morning, she found the car interior slightly damaged.

item.title: Canada lawmakers who knowingly helped other nations must be removed, party leader says
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Manhunt underway in Houston after inmate escapes from courthouse
item.description: The inmate escaped during a routine court appearance in downtown Houston, the Harris County Sheriff's office said.

item.title: Trump in Washington for meetings with Republican allies
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is back in Washington for the first time since becoming the presumptive Republican nominee as well as a convicted felon. Follow here for the latest live news updates.

item.title: Tony Bennett's daughters sue their brother over his handling of the late singer's assets
item.description: Tony Bennett’s two daughters are suing their brother, alleging he mishandled and failed to disclose some of their father’s assets in his role as trustee of the late singer’s estate

item.title: Retired L.A. County Sheriff's deputy goes missing while hiking on Greek island
item.description: Albert Calibet went missing on the Greek island of Armogos earlier this week.

item.title: What a medication abortion is like, according to a doctor
item.description: An expert in medication abortion describes how mifepristone and misoprostol work and what to expect after using these medications known as the "abortion pill."

item.title: 2 dead in single-engine plane crash in Northern California
item.description: Two people have been killed in a single-engine plane crash in Northern California

item.title: How hydroponic gardens in schools bring fresh produce to students
item.description: Public schools in Wisconsin are turning to indoor gardens to get fresh produce to their cafeteria tables.
